    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-11-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="84"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Perry</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 48.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-11-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 17, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>Your despatch of the 1st instant, No. 138, has
                    been received, together with the duplicates of your No. 131 and No. 134, which
                    accompanied it. You will perceive from my instructions of the 15th instant, No.
                    45, that your suggestion has been anticipated relative to the term of two months
                    fixed by Spain for the avoidance of hostile demonstrations towards Peru.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Horatio J. Perry</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic"
                            >c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic"
                            >c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Madrid.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
